# Setup and Installation

## Prerequisites
- Go 1.21 or later
- FFmpeg 4.0 or later
- Git
- Make (optional)

## Installation Steps

### 1. Clone the Repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-org/gooji.git
cd gooji
```

### 2. Install Dependencies
```bash
go mod download
```

### 3. Install FFmpeg
#### Ubuntu/Debian
```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install ffmpeg
```

#### macOS
```bash
brew install ffmpeg
```

#### Windows
Download from [FFmpeg website](mdc:https:/ffmpeg.org/download.html)

### 4. Build the Application
```bash
go build -o gooji
```

### 5. Configure the Application
Create a configuration file:
```yaml
server:
  port: 8080
  host: "0.0.0.0"

video:
  directory: "./videos"
  max_size: 100MB
  allowed_formats: [".mp4", ".webm"]

logging:
  level: "info"
  file: "gooji.log"
```

### 6. Run the Application
```bash
./gooji
```

## Development Setup

### Required Tools
- Go
- FFmpeg
- Node.js (for frontend development)
- Make (optional)

### Development Commands
```bash
# Run tests
go test ./...

# Build frontend assets
make build-frontend

# Run development server
make dev
```

## Environment Variables
- `GOOJI_VIDEO_DIR` - Video storage directory
- `GOOJI_PORT` - HTTP server port
- `GOOJI_LOG_LEVEL` - Logging level

## Directory Structure
```
gooji/
├── internal/         # Core application code
├── pkg/             # Shared packages
├── web/             # Frontend assets
│   ├── static/      # Static files
│   └── templates/   # HTML templates
├── videos/          # Video storage
└── config.yaml      # Configuration file
```

## Troubleshooting
- Check FFmpeg installation: `ffmpeg -version`
- Verify Go installation: `go version`
- Check file permissions for video directory
- Review application logs
- Ensure required ports are available
